This paper presents a method to improve the accuracy of a zero-velocity-aided inertial navigation system (INS) using a long short-term memory (LSTM) neural network. The paper focuses on the application of the method in human localization tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of a neural network for zero-velocity detection suggests a machine learning approach, which is commonly associated with sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves data analysis and signal processing, which could be categorized under statistics and machine learning (cs.SD).
